Reports indicate that individuals are facing difficulties with sending messages, establishing connections, and utilizing call functionalities on both the mobile application and the web-based platform. description: Baisakhi, a significant festival in North India, especially Punjab, marks the Sikh New Year and the harvest season. It commemorates the formation of the Khalsa Panth by Guru Gobind Singh Ji in 1699, a pivotal moment in Sikh history. Celebrations include vibrant cultural performances, fairs, and prayers for a prosperous harvest, bringing communities together in joy and gratitude.

description: The Supreme Court has ruled that neither the President nor the governor has absolute veto power over state bills. They must provide reasons for withholding assent. The court set timelines for decisions on bills. Governors have one month for assent or three months to refer the bill. The President also has three months to decide.

description: Delhi's IGIA faced significant disruptions as over 350 flights were delayed due to ongoing air traffic congestion, impacting operations for a second consecutive day. IndiGo confirmed that flights are being held due to congestion, affecting its network.

description: A political dispute has erupted over Tahawwur Rana's extradition to India, with Congress claiming credit for initiating the process during the UPA government. description: A devastating explosion at an aluminum foil factory in Umred MIDC, Nagpur district, claimed the lives of five individuals. description: Mayawati has questioned the silence of the leader of opposition on the Waqf Amendment Bill. She says both Congress and BJP have failed the Dalit community. description: Virender Sehwag criticised MS Dhoni's brief innings during Chennai Super Kings' crushing defeat to Kolkata Knight Riders, dismissing any notion that Dhoni's presence could have salvaged the innings. description: Congress leader Udit Raj casts doubt on the extradition of Tahawwur Rana, a key accused in the 26/11 Mumbai attacks, labelling it a 'game' and questioning his significant role. description: Despite Rishabh Pant's struggle to find batting form, Lucknow Super Giant have secured three wins out of five matches. Nicholas Pooran and Mitchell Marsh will once again be the key players for LSG when they take on Gujarat Titans on Saturday.

Separately, in Kishtwar, security forces eliminated three Pakistani terrorists during a joint operation, recovering a cache of weapons.
title: Pak violates ceasefire along LoC, Army JCO killed during encounter with terrorists

description: Following MNS protests against Hindi signage at a Mumbai Metro construction site, MMRDA began replacing it with Marathi. MNS now plans to target educational institutions, demanding prominent Marathi name boards. This comes after bank unions alleged intimidation by individuals claiming to be MNS members during a previous language campaign, even as Raj Thackeray paused the bank-focused efforts.
title: 'Replaced with Marathi': Hindi out at metro site in Thane district

description: A severe dust storm paralyzed flight operations at Delhi's IGI Airport, causing significant delays, diversions, and cancellations. Hundreds of passengers were stranded, leading to widespread complaints of airline mismanagement and mistreatment. Passengers voiced their frustration on social media, citing lack of information, constant rescheduling, and inadequate assistance from airline staff amidst the chaos.
title: 'Stampede-like situation at T3': Flight ops hit at Delhi Airport after dust storm

description: The White House defends Trump's tariffs as a necessary correction to decades of failed trade policies that harmed American workers and industry. Citing job losses and rising trade deficits, the administration highlights recent investments from major companies as evidence of the strategy's success. However, the tariff implementation has caused market disruption and criticism, raising questions about the long-term impact.
title: White House explains why Trump's tariffs were 'necessary'

description: NBA legend Isiah Thomas criticized LeBron James for practicing shirtless before a crucial game against the Houston Rockets, deeming it unprofessional and urging the NBA to fine him. Thomas argued that such behavior diminishes the league's professionalism. However, fans online largely disagreed with Thomas, with some calling him a hypocrite and defending James's pre-game routine.
title: 'Adam Silver if you wanna fine somebody, fine that': LeBron called out by Isiah

description: Hanuman Jayanti, celebrating Lord Hanuman's birth, falls on April 13, 2025, honoring his devotion, strength, and wisdom. Devotees observe fasts, chant prayers, and offer unique offerings like sindoor, seeking blessings for courage and protection. The day is auspicious for overcoming obstacles and pacifying negative influences, with temples hosting elaborate celebrations and continuous recitations.
title: Hanuman Jayanti 2025: Date, puja timings, and rituals

description: President Trump underwent his annual physical at Walter Reed, confidently stating he aced the cognitive test. While specifics remain private, a report promising transparency is expected soon. The 2018 evaluation revealed excellent cardiovascular health despite being overweight, with managed cholesterol. A past COVID-19 hospitalization adds context as the nation awaits the latest health update.
title: 'I got every answer right!' Trump claims perfect score in physical exam

description: Kolkata Knight Riders' spinners capitalized on a conducive Chennai pitch, dismantling CSK for their lowest total at Chepauk. Sunil Narine's explosive batting then sealed an emphatic eight-wicket victory, significantly boosting KKR's net run-rate.
title: IPL 2025: New low for MS Dhoni & Co

description: In a successful counter-terror operation in Jammu and Kashmir's Kishtwar district, the Indian Army has eliminated two Pakistani terrorists. The operation, conducted in the Chhatru area amidst challenging weather conditions, led to the recovery of a significant cache of weapons, including AK and M4 rifles.
title: J&K: Two terrorists killed in ongoing Kishtwar encounter
Madhya Pradesh Ladli Behna payout delayed; disbursement soon, say officials

description: Andrei Kozyrev, the first foreign minister of post-Soviet Russia and a vocal critic of Vladimir Putin, has been designated a "foreign agent" by Russia's justice ministry. The ministry accuses Kozyrev, who resides in the United States, of spreading false information about the government and military activities, particularly regarding the war in Ukraine.
title: Russia labels ex-foreign minister Andrei Kozyrev a 'foreign agent'

description: Fresh protests against the Waqf (Amendment) Act in West Bengal's Murshidabad district turned violent, with demonstrators torching vehicles in Jangipur. Security forces have been deployed to restore order, and the situation is reportedly under control. Prohibitory orders and internet suspensions are in place to curb further unrest, while the state government faces criticism over its handling of the situation.
title: Watch: Vehicles torched as Waqf protest turns violent in Murshidabad
La Nina over, India unlikely to see drought or extreme rain
Life term for ambulance driver who raped Covid patient on way to hospital
HCs should call in CBI only if they feel fair probe unlikely by state police: SC
Markets in India safe, people shouldn’t panic: Sebi chairman Tuhin Kanta Pandey

description: Amidst internal unrest and international pressure, US President Trump suggests Iran might be more receptive to discussions, emphasising diplomacy while warning of severe consequences if talks fail. Negotiations are planned in Muscat, involving US envoy Steve Witkoff and Iranian Deputy Foreign Minister Abbas Araghchi. Iran faces challenges with its proxies and economic sanctions, yet continues uranium enrichment, raising nuclear concerns.
title: Trump says Tehran may soften stance on nukes amid military and economic strain

description: Travis Kelce is reportedly prioritizing his football career in 2025, potentially his last season, by minimizing distractions, including his relationship with Taylor Swift. Following Super Bowl criticism, the couple has retreated from the spotlight, with Swift possibly taking a step back from attending games. Kelce aims to focus solely on football, seeking a standout season without off-field drama.
title: Why Taylor Swift is stepping back amid NFL comeback drive

description: In 2022, Elon Musk welcomed a recession to correct market excesses. Now, in 2025, President Trump's new tariffs are sparking recession fears, prompting warnings from economists and business leaders like Jamie Dimon. Despite his earlier stance, Musk now opposes the tariffs, advocating for free trade between the US and Europe, signaling a shift in his economic perspective.
title: 'Some bankruptcies need to happen': Musk's old recession quote resurfaces

description: A fire erupted at Parishkar Apartments in Ahmedabad, triggering a chaotic evacuation. Residents made daring escapes from balconies as flames engulfed the building's cable chute. Firefighters rescued eighteen people, some with minor injuries. The blaze, fueled by garbage and the building's power supply, caused extensive damage. Investigations are underway to determine the exact cause, and affected families are receiving assistance.
title: Watch: Woman drops kids from balcony as fire rages in Ahmedabad highrise
BJP, ADMK renew tie-up for Tamil Nadu polls next year
PM Modi expected to host Vances for meal; US VP's visit said to be private

description: A 34-year study by IMD and IITM reveals a concerning trend of increasingly acidic rainfall in India, particularly in Visakhapatnam, Prayagraj, and Mohanbari. While not yet critical, declining pH levels indicate rising acidity due to industrial and urban pollution. Pune shows a significant pH decrease, while natural dust neutralizes acidity in Jodhpur and Srinagar.
title: Air pollution turning India’s rainfall more acidic, shows study
